						               													<description>Wild Weather is a lightweight, portable card game for 2-4 players that plays in 15 mins.  Designed as part of the Standing in a Line Design Contest.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The aim of the game is to collect sets of cards that match a given objective card.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Players are dealt a hand of cards - all cards are displayed so all players may see the face in-play and have 4 Seasons - Winter, Spring, Summer, Fall and 4 Colours - Red, Blue, Yellow, Green, plus Symbols that are Black or White.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;On a Turn the player Chooses a TYPE (Season or Colour) and an ACTION (Flip Over, Pass-Left, Pass-Right). ALL cards matching the nominated TYPE are affected, in all hands.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Play continues clockwise until any player meets the objective - they take the card and a new Objective is revealed.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Game ends when the 5th Objective Card is won - scores added and winner declared.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game is also language independent and color-blind friendly.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
